======================================================================
COMPLETENESS AND BETA_2: TESTING NON-TOURNAMENTS
======================================================================

--- Part 1: Random oriented graphs on n=6 ---
  trial 128: beta_2=1, beta_1=0, edges=12
  trial 312: beta_2=1, beta_1=0, edges=12
  trial 318: beta_2=1, beta_1=0, edges=13
  trial 358: beta_2=1, beta_1=0, edges=12
  trial 460: beta_2=1, beta_1=0, edges=12
  beta_2 > 0 in 5/500 random oriented graphs (1.0%)

--- Part 2: Dense random digraphs on n=6 (every pair has at least one edge) ---
  beta_2 > 0 in 0/500 dense random digraphs

--- Part 3: Almost-tournaments on n=6 (1 edge removed) ---
  beta_2 > 0 in 13/500 almost-tournaments

--- Part 4: Tournament + 1 mutual edge on n=6 ---
  beta_2 > 0 in 0/500 tournament+mutual-edge

--- Part 5: Complete bidirectional graph on n=5,6 ---
  n=5: Complete bidirectional: bettis=[1, 0, 0, 0, 44]
  n=6: Complete bidirectional: bettis=[1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 265]

--- Part 6: Exhaustive check of COMPLETE ORIENTED graphs at n=4 ---
  n=4 tournaments: beta_2>0 in 0/64

--- Part 7: Complete digraphs (with possible mutual edges) at n=4 ---
    beta_2=1, edges=9, mutual_pairs=3
    beta_2=1, edges=9, mutual_pairs=3
    beta_2=1, edges=9, mutual_pairs=3
    beta_2=1, edges=9, mutual_pairs=3
    beta_2=1, edges=9, mutual_pairs=3
  n=4 complete digraphs: beta_2>0 in 24/729

--- Part 8: Sparse random digraphs at n=5 ---
  n=5 sparse (p=0.3): beta_2>0 in 14/500

--- SUMMARY ---

    beta_2 = 0 for ALL tournaments (complete oriented, exactly one edge per pair).
    beta_2 > 0 occurs in:
    - Sparse digraphs (missing edges allow cycles)
    - Dense digraphs with mutual edges (bidirectional pairs create new topology)
    - Almost-tournaments (removing even 1 edge can break beta_2=0)

    The COMPLETENESS + ANTISYMMETRY of tournaments is essential.
    
DONE.
